Message: CAPWAP-3-DISC_MAX_JOIN: "Rejecting %sdiscovery request from AP %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x - maximum AP joins

Message: DOT1X-1-AUTHENTICATOR_ERR: "Could not function as authenticator - %s
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error occurred in the 802.1X authentication process.

Message: DOT1X-1-INVALID_MDIE: "%s with %s MDIE IE received from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x. Expected MDID is: %x"
Explanation: Either MDIE is missing or invalid MDIE has been received as part of EAPOL-Key M2 message from the client. Fast transition cannot work if MDIE is not correctly received from the client.

Message: DOT1X-1-INVALID_PMK_ENTRY: "Not able to calculate PTK
Explanation: Not able to calculate PTK

Message: DOT1X-1-KEYDATA_PARSE_ERROR: Not able to parse KeyData field of %s for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Not able to parse KeyData field received as part of EAPOL-Key M2 message. Hence deauthenticate the client

Message: DOT1X-1-SET_BRDCST_KEY_ERR: "Could not set broadcast keys for WLAN %u
Explanation: Broadcast keys for the WLAN could not be set or refreshed because of an internal error.

Message: DOT1X-1-SOCK_OPER_FAILED: "Socket %s operation failed on 802.1X socket"
Explanation: An internal error caused a socket processing failure.

Message: DOT1X-1-TGRDATA_NOT_FOUND: "Out of memory! Unable to allocate memory for tgrData in mscb for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x. "
Explanation: Out of memory! Unable to allocate memory for tgrData in mscb.

Message: DOT1X-3-AAA_AUTH_SEND_FAIL: "Unable to send AAA message for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error prevented a message from being sent to the authentication server.
Recommended Action: Review the message log for other messages preceding this one that might indicate a connection failure or configuration problem. Ensure that the authentication servers are properly configured and are reachable.

Message: DOT1X-3-AAA_SEND_ERR: "Error sending AAA message - %s
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error prevented a message from being sent to the authentication server.

Message: DOT1X-3-ABORT_AUTH:  Authentication Aborted for  client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x Abort Reason:%s"
Explanation: An internal error caused 802.1X authentication to be canceled.

Message: DOT1X-3-ABORT_AUTH: " Authentication Aborted for  client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x Abort Reason:%s"
Explanation: An internal error caused 802.1X authentication to be canceleded.

Message: DOT1X-3-ADD_KEYMAP_KEY_ERR: "Unable to map RC4 key due to internal key buffer error
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error occurred when attempting to add the key mapping key to an EPOL-key message

Message: DOT1X-3-AUTHKEY_TX_TRANS_ERR: "Authentication state transition to state %u failed
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error occurred during authentication state transition.

Message: DOT1X-3-BAD_BUFFER_LENGTH: "Invalid buffer length in KDF function x:%d keyLen:%d outputLen:%d"
Explanation: Invalid buffer length while computing FT keys.

Message: DOT1X-3-CLIENT_NOT_FOUND: "Unable to process 802.1X %u msg - client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x not found"
Explanation: A message on an internal queue could not be processed because the client indicated in the message was not found in the internal database.

Message: DOT1X-3-COMPUTE_PRF_FAILED: "Failed to compute PRF mode %u
Explanation: An internal error occurred when attempting to calculate a pseudo-random value.

Message: DOT1X-3-EAP_MSG_ERR: "Could not process EAP message - %s
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an EAP message from the server or supplicant was not understood.

Message: DOT1X-3-EAPOL_MSG_ATTACK: "Possible authentication attack - %s
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an EAPOL message from the client contained data that should only be sent by the access point. This problem may be caused by an intruder spoofing authentication frames.

Message: DOT1X-3-GTK_ENCRYPT_FAILED: "Unable to encrypt CCKM GTK for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error occurred when attempting to encrypt a temporal key.

Message: DOT1X-3-INTF_CREATION_FAILED: "Unable to create 802.1X interface for AP: %s"
Explanation: AP's 802.1X interface was not allocated by WLC which is required for client association on dot1x WLAN. Hence Client association on dot1xWLAN with this AP will fail.

Message: DOT1X-3-INTF_DEL_FAILED: "Unable to delete 802.1X interface"
Explanation: An internal error prevented an 802.1X interface structure from being deleted.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_CLIENT_DOT1X_CB: "Missing 802.1X control block for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal control block was unexpectedly null.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_DOT1X_CB: "Missing 802.1X or client control block"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal control block was unexpectedly null.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_DOT1X_Q_TYPE: "Invalid type
Explanation: A message on an internal message queue could not be processed because the message type was invalid.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_EAPOL_VER: "Invalid EAPOL version
Explanation: Client authentication failed because of an authentication protocol error between the client and access point.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_ENCRYPTION: "Invalid encryption policy
Explanation: Invalid encryption policy for the client while processing FT reassociation request.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_KEY_LEN: "Invalid key length
Explanation: An internal error occurred when determining the key length for an encryption cipher.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_KEY_OUT_LEN: Invalid key length or mic length: Key Length: %d
Explanation: Invalid key length or mic length. Client needs to associate with the correct MIC.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_KEYWRAP_ARG: "Invalid key wrap parameters"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error caused invalid data to be passed to the key wrap algorithm.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_KEYWRAP_PKT: Received invalid keywrap packet - %s"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because a received keywrap packet was invalid.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_MIC_ALGORITHM: " unsupported MIC algorithm
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error occurred when attempting to compute a MIC value.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_PTK_LEN: "Invalid PTK Key length
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error occurred when attempting to compute a temporal key.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_RC4_KEY: "Invalid EAPOL RC4 key msg from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x - %s"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an EAPOL RC4 key message from the client contained invalid data.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_REPLAY_CTR: "Invalid replay counter from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x - got %02x %02x %02x %02x %02x %02x %02x %02x
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an EAPOL message from the client contained an invalid replay counter.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_WPA_KEY_MSG: "Error in received EAPOL msg - %s
Explanation: Client authentication failed because of an authetication protocol error between the client and access point

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_WPA_KEY_MSG_STATE: "Received invalid %s msg in %s state - %s
Explanation: Client authentication failed because of an authentication protocol error between the client and access point.

Message: DOT1X-3-INVALID_WPA_KEY_STATE: "Received EAPOL-key message while in invalid state
Explanation: An authentication message was received from a client that was not expected while in the current state. The message was ignored

Message: DOT1X-3-KDF_BAD_BUFFER: "Bad buffer length for function x:%d keyLen:%d outputLen:%d"
Explanation: Error while calcualting PTK using KDF algo. for11r or 11w capable clients.

Message: DOT1X-3-KDF_BAD_INPUT_LENGTH: "Input length req is %d
Explanation: Error while calcualting PTK using KDF algo. for11r or 11w capable clients as Input Key Len is wrong.

Message: DOT1X-3-KEY_LEN_NOT_FOUND: "Key length not found for policy %u"
Explanation: An internal error occurred when attempting to determine the key length for an encrypted policy.

Message: DOT1X-3-MOBILE_EXCESS_RUN: "Authentication has run more than %u times - deleting client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the authentication process failed to complete within the maximum permitted number of attempts.

Message: DOT1X-3-PMKR1NAME_VERIFICATION_FAILURE: "Not able to verify PMKR1Name in %s for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Not able to verify PMKR1Name for the client. Try client association again.

Message: DOT1X-3-PREAUTH_ENTRY_NOT_FOUND: "PreAuth entry is not found for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x while processing FT Reassociation request."
Explanation: Preauth Entry is not found while processing FT Reassociation request. The PMK Cache needs to contain this information for Fast transition to occur.

Message: DOT1X-3-PREPARE_KEY_M5_ERR: "Unable to create EAPOL-key M5 for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x- group key not found for WLAN %u"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an internal error occurred when attempting to create an EAPOL-key message

Message: DOT1X-3-PSK_CONFIG_ERR: "Client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x may be using an incorrect PSK"
Explanation: A client may be attempting to access the network with an improperly configured PSK.

Message: DOT1X-3-RCV_INVALID_CCX_IE: "%s with %s CCX IE received from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because of an authentication protocol error between the client and access point

Message: DOT1X-3-RCV_INVALID_SFA_IE: "%s with %s SFA IE received from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because of an authentication protocol error between the client and access point

Message: DOT1X-3-SEND_WPA_BUFF_ERR: "Unable to send EAPOL-key - buffer is too small
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the retransmit buffer was too small to store the outbound authentication message.

Message: DOT1X-3-STICK_CACHE_SIZE_EXCEEDED: "Sticky cache can't be supported for 9th AP.Client MAC %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x."
Explanation: WLC supports only 8 PMKIDs support and hence fast roam can't be supported on 9th AP onwards.
Recommended Action: Sticky Caching supports only upto 8 PMKIDs .

Message: DOT1X-3-UNKNOWN_EAPOL_KEY_DESC: "Received unknown EAPOL key descriptor %u from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x "
Explanation: Client authentication failed because an EAPOL message from the client contained an invalid or unsupported key descriptor.

Message: DOT1X-3-USER_LOGIN_DENY: "Authentication rejected for user %s - user may already be logged in"
Explanation: User authentication failed. The most likely cause is that the user name is already in use by another client.
Recommended Action: Ensure that unique user names are used by each client.

Message: DOT1X-3-WPA_KEY_MIC_ERR: "TKIP MIC errors reported in EAPOL key msg from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the client reported TKIP MIC errors in an EAPOL key message that it received from the controller. The problem might be caused by an intruder and countermeasures may be taken.

Message: DOT1X-3-WPA_SEND_STATE_ERR: "Unable to send EAPOL-key msg - invalid WPA state
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the session was not in the correct state when attempting to send an EAPOL-key message.

Message: DOT1X-4-AAA_MAX_RETRY: "Max AAA authentication attempts exceeded for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the maximum number of authentication attempts permitted by the authentication was exceeded. If Block listing is configured the client will be block listed.

Message: DOT1X-4-BE_RCV_NULL_ARG: "Empty message received from AAA"
Explanation: A AAA message with no content was received by the AAA back-end process  The message was ignored.

Message: DOT1X-4-DOT1X_MAX_RETRY: "Max authentication attempts exceeded for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the maximum number of retries was exceeded.

Message: DOT1X-4-EAP_CLIENT_NO_RETRANS: "EAP packet is too long for retransmission"
Explanation: An EAP message was sent to the client but is too large to be stored in the retransmission queue. If the message is not acknowledged as having been received by the client it will not be retransmitted.

Message: DOT1X-4-IGNORE_PREAUTH: "Ignoring pre-auth request from client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: A pre-authentication request message from a client was ignored

Message: DOT1X-4-INTF_NOT_FOUND: "Unable to find 802.1X interface for AP %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the AP's 802.1X interface was not found. This may have been caused by sudden loss of connection to the AP
Recommended Action: The system has failed to allocate some memory. The system might be out of buffers. This may be temporary problem

Message: DOT1X-4-INVALID_EAP_MSG: "Invalid EAP message received - %s
Explanation: An invalid EAP message was received from the client. The message was ignored.

Message: DOT1X-4-INVALID_MSG_TYPE: "Invalid message '%s'
Explanation: A message was received from AAA with an unexpected type. The message was ignored.

Message: DOT1X-4-MAX_EAP_RETRANS: "Max EAP retransmissions exceeded for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"

Message: DOT1X-4-MAX_EAP_RETRIES: "Max EAP identity request retries
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the maximum number of permitted attempts was exceeded.

Message: DOT1X-4-MAX_EAPOL_KEY_RETRANS: "Max EAPOL-key M%u retransmissions exceeded for client %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: Client authentication failed because the client did not respond to an EAPOL-key message.

Explanation: An EAPOL packet with an unknown type was received from a client. The packet was ignored.

Explanation: A AAA message with no content was received. The message was ignored.

Explanation: A discovery response could not be sent to an AP because the controller was not able to obtain the IP address of the AP manager interface.
Recommended Action: Correct the AP manager interface configuration.

Message: LWAPP-3-DISC_AP_MGR_ERR2: "The system is unable to process primary discovery request from AP
Explanation: A discovery response could not be sent to an AP because the controller was not able to obtain the IP address of the AP manager interface.
Recommended Action: Correct the AP manager interface configuration.

Explanation: The controller ignored a broadcast discovery request from an AP because the AP is not on the same subnet as the controller.

Message: LWAPP-3-DISC_INTF_ERR1: "Ignoring discovery request received on non-management interface
Explanation: A discovery request from an AP was ignored because it was received on an invalid interface. The Network configuration may be invalid.
Recommended Action: Check the network configuration to ensure that packets from the AP are correctly routed.

Message: LWAPP-3-DISC_INTF_ERR2: "Ignoring discovery request received on a wrong VLAN

Explanation: An error has occurred in the regulatory domain information for the slots on the AP. All of them do not have regulatory domain configured. The AP might not be able to join the controller.

Message: LWAPP-3-RD_ERR3: "The system detects an invalid regulatory domain
Explanation: The regulatory domain configured on the AP slot was not understood. The AP might not be able to join the controller.
Recommended Action: Check if the correct country code is configured on the controller

Message: LWAPP-3-RD_ERR4: "The system detects an invalid regulatory domain %s for AP %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x"
Explanation: The regulatory domain configured on the AP was not understood. The AP might not be able to join the controller.
Recommended Action: Check if the correct country code is configured on the controller

Message: LWAPP-3-RD_ERR5: "AP's

Message: LWAPP-3-RD_ERR6: APs
Explanation: Due to an error in the regulatory domain configured on the AP
Recommended Action: Check if the correct country code is configured on the controller.

Message: LWAPP-3-RD_ERR8: Country code
Explanation: Due to an error in the regulatory domain configured on the AP

Message: LWAPP-3-RD_ERR9: "APs %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x country code changed from
Explanation: The country code associated with the regulatory domain configured on the AP was incorrect,If the AP is functioning correctly with the changed country code

Explanation: The Maximum number of times that an LWAPP control packet is transmitted before declaring the AP dead has been reached for this AP. The AP may not be on the network.
